column3: Oh. Well, this is a really nice place. You should stay a bit.
Maybe. How long have you lived here?
You know this place isn't real, right?
What are you talking about? You sound crazy. Heh.
I mean, this isn't real life.
Oh, sure. And I'm your great-aunt Linda!
What? You mean like in Inception? You must watch too many movies.
You made this place up to deal with your loneliness.
Can you tell me where you lived before you moved here?

No. I mean, I think most of the others lived in this area over yonder, but it grew unstable and we've had to put a gate around it to keep people from wandering off and getting hurt. But I digress. I don't think I've ever lived anywhere else, personally.
Doesn't that strike you as odd?
What if I could prove it to you?
I could go find the area you mentioned.
I wouldn't recommend it. It's dangerous.
...You're one of those people who explores abandoned buildings for fun, aren't you?
See you in a bit then.
